CatDescriptText: Wilbur C. Douglass, Wendell Stanton, Paul Jones, Richard Jones, Joe Givens, and Homer Brown were lawyers, Everett Utterback was manager of the City Housing Authority (1941).  Thomas Barton, another lawyer, served as president of the Urban League of Pittsburgh from 1942-1952 and as an Assistant City Solicitor from 1938.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, front row from left: Richard Jones, Homer Brown, Everett Utterback Sr.; back row: Thomas Barton, Paul Jones, Joe Givens, Wilbur Douglass Sr., unknown man, and Wendell Stanton, posed in interior
